.\" Man page for wxmine(6) -- wxWidgets Minesweeper clone.
.\" Content adapted from the bundled Windows CHM / macOS Help Book.
.TH WXMINE 6 "2026-04-19" "wxmine 1.0" "Games"
.SH NAME
wxmine \- wxWidgets Minesweeper clone
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B wxmine
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B wxmine
is a cross-platform port of the classic Microsoft Minesweeper game built on
wxWidgets. The object is to correctly mark all the mines hidden on the board
as quickly as possible without uncovering one.
.PP
You are presented with a mine field simulated by a grid of covered squares.
Uncover squares that do not contain mines and mark squares that do. If you
uncover every non-mine square you win; if you uncover a mine, you lose. The
faster you play, the lower (better) your score.
.PP
The counter in the upper-left of the playing area shows the number of
remaining unmarked mines (it decreases by one every time you mark a square
as a mine, even if the mark is incorrect). The counter in the upper-right
is a timer, in seconds, which starts when you uncover the first square.
.SH PLAYING THE GAME
.SS Choosing a skill level
From the
.B Game
menu choose
.BR Beginner ,
.BR Intermediate ,
or
.BR Expert .
Higher skill levels use a larger mine field with more mines.
.SS Starting a new game
From the
.B Game
menu choose
.B New
or press
.BR F2 .
You can also click the yellow "happy face" at the top of the board.
.SS Locating the mines
.TP
1.
To uncover a square, click it with the left mouse button. If the square is a
mine, you lose.
.TP
2.
If the square is not a mine, a number appears. That number is the count of
mines in the eight surrounding squares.
.TP
3.
To mark a square as a mine, click it with the right mouse button.
.TP
4.
To mark a square you are uncertain about, click it with the right mouse
button twice. This marks it with a question mark (?). Later you can either
mark it as a mine or uncover it.
.SH RULES
.IP \(bu 2
The playing area is a grid of covered squares. Uncover squares until only
those containing mines are covered.
.IP \(bu 2
An uncovered square either shows a number
.IR N ,
meaning there are
.I N
mines in the surrounding eight squares, or is blank, meaning there are none.
.IP \(bu 2
If you uncover a blank square, the surrounding eight squares are
uncovered automatically because none of them can contain a mine.
.IP \(bu 2
If you uncover a square that contains a mine, the game ends and every mine
is revealed.
.PP
You can also "clear around" an uncovered numbered square whose adjacent mines
have already been marked.
.SS Clearing around a square
Point to the numbered square and click both mouse buttons at the same time.
.IP \(bu 2
Clearing only works if you have already marked exactly the right number of
mines around the square. If too few mines are marked, or if the square is
still covered, nothing happens.
.IP \(bu 2
If you marked the wrong squares and clearing exposes a real mine, the game
ends.
.SH MARKING A SQUARE
.TP
.B Uncover a square
Left\-click the square.
.TP
.B Mark a square as a mine
Right\-click the square once.
.TP
.B Mark a square as a question mark
Right\-click the square twice (from an unmarked state).
.TP
.B Clear a mark
Right\-click the square again until it cycles back to unmarked.
.SH SCORING
Scoring is time\-based. The timer in the upper\-right of the playing area
shows your elapsed time in seconds. The faster you find all the mines, the
better your score. Choose
.B Best Times
from the
.B Game
menu to see a list of your fastest playing times per skill level.
.SH STRATEGY
.IP \(bu 2
If an uncovered square is labeled
.B 1
and it touches exactly one covered square, that covered square must be a
mine.
.IP \(bu 2
If an uncovered square already has the correct number of adjacent mines
marked, clear around it to expose the rest of its neighbours safely.
.IP \(bu 2
Do not guess. If you cannot work out a move, approach the area from a
different direction, or mark ambiguous squares with question marks while you
think.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/wxmine/
Per\-user preferences and high\-score tables.
.SH SEE ALSO
The full HTML help (identical content with illustrations) is bundled as
.IR wxmine.chm
on Windows and as the
.I wxmine.help
Apple Help Book on macOS.
.SH AUTHORS
Original Minesweeper by Microsoft Corporation. wxWidgets port and packaging
